The paper deals with the construction of fast-decodable space-time block codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of nonassociative algebras is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.NA (nonassociative algebra). The paper also discusses the properties of the codes in terms of their diversity and decoding complexity, which could fall under cs.SI (signal processing and communications), cs.CR (cryptography and security), or cs.LG (machine learning).
